The son of late General Murtala Muhammed, Abba Risqua Muhammed, has lauded President Muhammadu Buhari for his fight against corruption, urging Nigerians to support him to succeed. He spoke during the unveiling of the statue of his late father at the entrance of the Postgraduate hall of residence at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife, which was named after him. Muhammed noted that his father fearlessly fought corruption during his tenure in office as the Head of State of Nigeria and lauded Buhari for doing the same. Dad left only N7,000 in his account as former Head of State – Murtala Muhammed's son Buhari: Late Murtala was a man in a hurry Murtala’s death Derailed Nigeria  – Buhari